# 5. Design Principles

The backend follows several software engineering principles.

## Separation of Concerns

Each service performs one task.

Examples

* ScoreService only manages scores.
* RegistrationService only manages registrations.
* FirebaseService only communicates with Firebase.

---

## Single Responsibility Principle

Each class has one responsibility.

Example

```
ScoreService

Only updates scores.
```

instead of

```
ScoreService

Updates scores

Reads Google Sheets

Generates QR codes

Authenticates users
```

---

## Encapsulation

Business logic is hidden behind service methods.

Controllers never manipulate data directly.

---

## Loose Coupling

Services communicate through interfaces rather than depending directly on one another.

This improves maintainability and testing.

