# 10. Business Rules

The backend enforces several business rules.

Examples

* Team names must be unique.
* Scores cannot become negative.
* Registration closes after the deadline.
* Only administrators may modify scores.
* Teams require at least one member.

---

# 11. Error Handling

The backend validates all operations.

Examples

Invalid password

↓

Display authentication error

---

Duplicate team

↓

Reject registration

---

Firebase unavailable

↓

Display connection error

---

Google Sheets unavailable

↓

Retry connection

---

# 12. Data Validation

Validation occurs before any data is saved.

Examples

Team

* Name cannot be empty.
* Team name must be unique.

Members

* Name cannot be blank.

Scores

* Must be numeric.
* Cannot be negative.

